<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>About the Gallery</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>About This Website</h1>
        <p>Learn why this Spider-Man movie character gallery was created.</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a href="/characters">Home</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/characters/create">Add a Character</a>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <section class="about-box">

            <img src="images/spiderman.jpg" alt="Spider-Man Movies">

            <h2>Purpose of the Website</h2>

            <p>
                The theme I chose is based on characters from the Spider-Man movies because the movies include
                heroes, villains, family members, and supporting characters.
            </p>

            <p>
                I wanted the site to be easy to read and simple to use. The home page shows different character
                cards, the details page gives more information about Spider-Man, and the form page allows a user
                to pretend to add a new character to the gallery.
            </p>

            <p>
                The design uses red, black, white, and blue because those colors match the superhero style.
                The layout uses cards so each character is separated clearly and the website feels organized.
            </p>

            <a class="button-link" href="/characters">Return to Home Page</a>

        </section>
    </main>

</body>
</html>